{"abstract": "Consumer and labor groups hailed the moves by H&M, Zara and others after a building collapse in Bangladesh, saying they would increase pressure on other retailers.", "web_url": "https://www.nytimes.com/2013/05/14/business/global/hm-agrees-to-bangladesh-safety-plan.html", "snippet": "Consumer and labor groups hailed the moves by H&M, Zara and others after a building collapse in Bangladesh, saying they would increase pressure on other retailers.", "lead_paragraph": "Three weeks after a building collapse in Bangladesh that killed more than 1,100 workers, several of the world\u2019s largest apparel companies \u2013 including the retailing giant H&M and Inditex, owner of the Zara chain \u2014 agreed on Monday to sign a far-reaching and legally binding plan that requires retailers to help finance fire safety and building improvements in the factories they use in Bangladesh.", "source": "The New York Times", "multimedia": [{"rank": 0, "subtype": "xlarge", "caption": null, "credit": null, "type": "image", "url": "images/2013/05/14/business/global/14factories/14factories-articleLarge.jpg", "height": 403, "width": 600, "subType": "xlarge", "crop_name": "articleLarge", "legacy": {"xlarge": "images/2013/05/14/business/global/14factories/14factories-articleLarge.jpg", "xlargewidth": 600, "xlargeheight": 403}}, {"rank": 0, "subtype": "jumbo", "caption": null, "credit": null, "type": "image", "url": "images/2013/05/14/business/global/14factories/14factories-jumbo.jpg", "height": 687, "width": 1024, "subType": "jumbo", "crop_name": "jumbo", "legacy": {}}, {"rank": 0, "subtype": "superJumbo", "caption": null, "credit": null, "type": "image", "url": "images/2013/05/14/business/global/14factories/14factories-superJumbo.jpg", "height": 1374, "width": 2048, "subType": "superJumbo", "crop_name": "superJumbo", "legacy": {}}, {"rank": 0, "subtype": "thumbnail", "caption": null, "credit": null, "type": "image", "url": "images/2013/05/14/business/global/14factories/14factories-